<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2efe9); padding:80px 24px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#c4912a; margin-bottom:1rem;">Local Expertise</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#1c1917; margin-bottom:1.75rem;">Character streets meet a world-class urban renewal precinct.</h2>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      Kelvin Grove sits about two kilometres north-west of the CBD grid, and it has a split identity that makes it genuinely interesting to sell in. The older character streets hold traditional Queenslanders and Federation-era homes on blocks that are large by inner-Brisbane standards. Directly alongside them, the Kelvin Grove Urban Village at QUT has created a dense, walkable precinct that functions like a small city centre within the suburb.
    </p>
<!-- APPRAISAL FORM -->
